cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and intrinsic image decomposition, which are typically studied in the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). The paper proposes a supervised end-to-end CNN architecture to jointly learn intrinsic image decomposition and semantic segmentation, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also creates a dataset of synthetic images of natural environments, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) subfields.
